    "Comments": {
      "text": "Bactrim dosing is based on the trimethoprim part not the sulfamethoxazole part.\nThe dosing in 8-10mg/kg of trimethoprim divided q12 hours (4-5 mg/kg per dose).\nThe concentration of Bactrim is 200 mg of sulfamethoxazole and 40 mg of trimethoprim in 5 mL.\nExample: 10 kg child - 8mg/kg per day of trimethoprim part which is 80 mg per day. Divide by 2 = 40 mg of trimethoprim per dose. Based on the above concentration patient will get 5 mL of Bactrim 2 times per day.",
      "subsections": {},
